who's very knowledgeable

00:01:57.384 --> 00:01:59.987 align:middle line:84%
about commodities marketing
precious metals tried

00:01:59.987 --> 00:02:01.288 align:middle line:84%
to interest me, and I
said, "Well, you know,

00:02:01.288 --> 00:02:03.457 align:middle line:84%
I have no background in
precious metals," and he said,

00:02:03.457 --> 00:02:06.627 align:middle line:84%
"I just want you to watch
the market," and I started

00:02:06.627 --> 00:02:09.230 align:middle line:84%
to watch the price of
gold for about 3 days,

00:02:09.230 --> 00:02:10.698 align:middle line:84%
and I called him back,
and I said, "You know,

00:02:10.698 --> 00:02:12.833 align:middle line:84%
I don't know anything
about precious metals,

00:02:12.833 --> 00:02:15.369 align:middle line:84%
but I have to tell you, I
know a lot about markets.

00:02:15.369 --> 00:02:17.705 align:middle line:84%
There's no way a market
can behave like this."

00:02:17.705 --> 00:02:18.606 align:middle line:90%
This is...

00:02:18.606 --> 00:02:21.675 align:middle line:90%
This is a managed situation.

00:02:21.675 --> 00:02:25.713 align:middle line:84%
This is not a market, and
we've watched that in sector

00:02:25.713 --> 00:02:27.381 align:middle line:90%
after sector, particularly

00:02:27.381 --> 00:02:30.618 align:middle line:84%
as we've centralized both
the control of capital

00:02:30.618 --> 00:02:33.053 align:middle line:84%
and we've centralized
different industries.

00:02:33.053 --> 00:02:37.524 align:middle line:84%
What you're watching is an
integration of national security

00:02:37.524 --> 00:02:41.662 align:middle line:84%
and geopolitical strategy with
financial markets and economics,

00:02:41.662 --> 00:02:46.600 align:middle line:84%
and so oftentimes you'll see the
oil price managed or the price

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:50.504 align:middle line:84%
of gold managed for
geopolitical strategic reasons

00:02:50.504 --> 00:02:53.274 align:middle line:84%
that if you were the Secretary
of the Treasury, you know,

00:02:53.274 --> 00:02:54.875 align:middle line:84%
you would think was
the right thing to do,

00:02:54.875 --> 00:02:58.746 align:middle line:84%
but the global game is causing
a management that if you're

00:02:58.746 --> 00:03:02.082 align:middle line:84%
in the market trying to
deal with fundamentals,

00:03:02.082 --> 00:03:04.718 align:middle line:84%
it's just Orwellian,
and, of course, you know,

00:03:04.718 --> 00:03:07.054 align:middle line:84%
it's very difficult
in these environments

00:03:07.054 --> 00:03:09.957 align:middle line:84%
to get adequate information
about what's going on.

00:03:09.957 --> 00:03:11.759 align:middle line:90%
So it can be very mind numbing

00:03:11.759 --> 00:03:14.728 align:middle line:84%
for the retail investor
who's just trying

00:03:14.728 --> 00:03:16.764 align:middle line:84%
to make sensible
decisions, and up is down,

00:03:16.764 --> 00:03:18.165 align:middle line:90%
and down is up, and, you know...

00:03:18.165 --> 00:03:19.400 align:middle line:90%
That is what it's like.

00:03:19.400 --> 00:03:21.435 align:middle line:84%
It's like dropping down
the rabbit hole, [laughter]

00:03:21.435 --> 00:03:23.170 align:middle line:90%
and the funny thing, I mean...

00:03:23.170 --> 00:03:25.906 align:middle line:84%
Financial puzzle powers
is what I call it.

00:03:25.906 --> 00:03:27.107 align:middle line:90%
[Laughter] Exactly.

00:03:27.107 --> 00:03:29.109 align:middle line:84%
Didn't it used to be
something kind of like this?

00:03:29.109 --> 00:03:31.011 align:middle line:84%
I mean if there never
was any kind of market

00:03:31.011 --> 00:03:35.649 align:middle line:84%
that when you had an upside in
the stock market, you had kind

00:03:35.649 --> 00:03:38.619 align:middle line:84%
of a downside in metals, and
when the market went down,

00:03:38.619 --> 00:03:40.421 align:middle line:90%
metals went up, and it seemed

00:03:40.421 --> 00:03:42.256 align:middle line:84%
to have its own little
balancing act,

00:03:42.256 --> 00:03:44.124 align:middle line:84%
which has long since
disappeared.

00:03:44.124 --> 00:03:47.127 align:middle line:84%
Was that ever real, or
was that manipulated, too?

00:03:47.127 --> 00:03:48.495 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think to
a certain extent,

00:03:48.495 --> 00:03:51.965 align:middle line:84%
there's always been a balance
of fundamental economics

00:03:51.965 --> 00:03:53.567 align:middle line:90%
and markets with management.

00:03:53.567 --> 00:03:54.901 align:middle line:90%
But not anymore.

00:03:54.901 --> 00:03:58.472 align:middle line:84%
Now even those basic kind of
factors don't seem to align.

00:03:58.472 --> 00:03:59.406 align:middle line:90%
Here's what's interesting.

00:03:59.406 --> 00:04:01.575 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the
people managing,

00:04:01.575 --> 00:04:03.977 align:middle line:84%
fundamental economics
absolutely matter to them.

00:04:03.977 --> 00:04:05.079 align:middle line:90%
They are optimizers.

00:04:05.079 --> 00:04:05.913 align:middle line:90%
You have to be.

00:04:05.913 --> 00:04:06.947 align:middle line:90%
It's a big planet.

00:04:06.947 --> 00:04:08.382 align:middle line:90%
There are a lot of people,

00:04:08.382 --> 00:04:10.751 align:middle line:84%
and so you can't keep
a price, you know.

00:04:10.751 --> 00:04:13.520 align:middle line:84%
If there's more and more
people and less and less land

00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:17.190 align:middle line:84%
to grow wheat on, you can't keep
the price of wheat down forever.

00:04:17.190 --> 00:04:19.860 align:middle line:84%
So fundamentals matter
to everybody,

00:04:19.860 --> 00:04:22.429 align:middle line:90%
but we do see these situations

00:04:22.429 --> 00:04:24.999 align:middle line:84%
where you get enormous
intervention,

00:04:24.999 --> 00:04:28.335 align:middle line:84%
not just of governments, but
of various private cartels,

00:04:28.335 --> 00:04:31.939 align:middle line:84%
and we're watching an
integration of economic warfare,

00:04:31.939 --> 00:04:35.008 align:middle line:84%
of literally warfare with
financial markets, and,

00:04:35.008 --> 00:04:38.345 align:middle line:84%
of course, what's happened
as we've centralized

00:04:38.345 --> 00:04:42.516 align:middle line:84%
and as we've globalized, digital
technology gives us the ability

00:04:42.516 --> 00:04:44.385 align:middle line:84%
to now create things
like derivatives,

00:04:44.385 --> 00:04:48.188 align:middle line:84%
which gives us the
ability to manage

00:04:48.188 --> 00:04:49.957 align:middle line:84%
in powerful ways we
never could before.

00:04:49.957 --> 00:04:52.459 align:middle line:84%
So we see interest rates
coming down, down, down.

00:04:52.459 --> 00:04:53.761 align:middle line:90%
It's like the limbo dance.

00:04:53.761 --> 00:04:55.362 align:middle line:90%
How low can they go?

00:04:55.362 --> 00:04:58.499 align:middle line:84%
And if you look, in fact,
at the books of derivatives,

00:04:58.499 --> 00:05:01.568 align:middle line:84%
the vast majority are
interest rate swaps,

00:05:01.568 --> 00:05:03.570 align:middle line:84%
and that technology is
giving you the ability

00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:06.573 align:middle line:84%
to do these things in ways
that many participants

00:05:06.573 --> 00:05:08.375 align:middle line:84%
in the market are
not familiar with.

00:05:08.375 --> 00:05:10.277 align:middle line:84%
You know, it kind
of snuck up on them.

00:05:10.277 --> 00:05:15.516 align:middle line:84%
So it's absolutely changing, and
what it means is that you need

00:05:15.516 --> 00:05:21.755 align:middle line:84%
to have a real picture of your
world, which is of an ecosystem.

00:05:21.755 --> 00:05:24.625 align:middle line:84%
Right. So I need to be
able to look, you know,

00:05:24.625 --> 00:05:27.261 align:middle line:84%
when I grew up there were people
who read the New York Times

00:05:27.261 --> 00:05:29.463 align:middle line:84%
and were interested in
policy, and there were people

00:05:29.463 --> 00:05:31.498 align:middle line:84%
who read the Wall Street Journal
and were interested in markets,

00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:33.666 align:middle line:84%
and the two were totally
separate universes

00:05:33.666 --> 00:05:35.669 align:middle line:84%
and had nothing to do
with each other, you know.

00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:38.872 align:middle line:84%
Right. And now what we're
talking about is an integration

00:05:38.872 --> 00:05:41.208 align:middle line:84%
where whether it's
political management

00:05:41.208 --> 00:05:44.478 align:middle line:84%
or market fundamentals, you
need to integrate both of them,

00:05:44.478 --> 00:05:47.648 align:middle line:84%
and you need to be able to
see the world as an ecosystem,

00:05:47.648 --> 00:05:50.918 align:middle line:84%
a living system on
an integrated basis,

00:05:50.918 --> 00:05:53.654 align:middle line:84%
and if you've been educated
in our system, you know,

00:05:53.654 --> 00:05:54.788 align:middle line:90%
there are places in the world

00:05:54.788 --> 00:05:57.291 align:middle line:84%
where people are educated
to think that way.

00:05:57.291 --> 00:05:59.927 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's not a big
deal here if you've come

00:05:59.927 --> 00:06:02.095 align:middle line:84%
up in your little box and
you're very knowledgeable

00:06:02.095 --> 00:06:04.531 align:middle line:84%
in your little box,
it's very shocking.

00:06:04.531 --> 00:06:05.732 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it is.

