00:10:10.811 --> 00:10:13.280 align:middle line:84%
to start flushing out private
ownership of gold, too.

00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:15.682 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people freaked
out and started selling.

00:10:15.682 --> 00:10:18.418 align:middle line:84%
Right. Well if you want to bring
in a lot of inventory fast,

00:10:18.418 --> 00:10:19.119 align:middle line:90%
this is how you do it.

00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:20.087 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, crash the price.

00:10:20.087 --> 00:10:21.922 align:middle line:84%
You crash the price,
but let's look

00:10:21.922 --> 00:10:24.591 align:middle line:90%
at financial stability globally.

00:10:24.591 --> 00:10:27.694 align:middle line:84%
We have had for many decades
what's called a long term bull

00:10:27.694 --> 00:10:29.129 align:middle line:90%
market in bonds.

00:10:29.129 --> 00:10:31.965 align:middle line:84%
Interest rates have been
coming down, down, down,

00:10:31.965 --> 00:10:35.435 align:middle line:84%
and that has put a floor
in the price of bonds.

00:10:35.435 --> 00:10:38.772 align:middle line:84%
We've seen tremendous investment
both institutional and retail go

00:10:38.772 --> 00:10:43.043 align:middle line:84%
into bonds, and everyone's
looking at this huge bond market

00:10:43.043 --> 00:10:45.011 align:middle line:84%
because we've been printing,
printing, printing, printing,

00:10:45.011 --> 00:10:47.214 align:middle line:90%
printing, and saying, you know,

00:10:47.214 --> 00:10:50.584 align:middle line:84%
interest rates can't go
much lower, so what's going

00:10:50.584 --> 00:10:51.985 align:middle line:90%
to happen when this turns?

00:10:51.985 --> 00:10:55.222 align:middle line:84%
Right. And, of course, there are
several things that can happen.

00:10:55.222 --> 00:10:59.326 align:middle line:84%
One thing is we can literally do
a planetary debt for equity swap

00:10:59.326 --> 00:11:02.496 align:middle line:84%
and move money into the equity
markets and shift the model,

00:11:02.496 --> 00:11:05.999 align:middle line:84%
shift, you know, be on an
equity model, but, you know,

00:11:05.999 --> 00:11:07.934 align:middle line:90%
that's the nice solution.

00:11:07.934 --> 00:11:09.636 align:middle line:90%
That would be the nice result.

00:11:09.636 --> 00:11:13.173 align:middle line:84%
The not so nice is everybody
rushes for safety to get

00:11:13.173 --> 00:11:14.875 align:middle line:84%
out of the bond market
if interest...

00:11:14.875 --> 00:11:18.445 align:middle line:84%
because if interest rates
turn, let alone turn sharply,

00:11:18.445 --> 00:11:21.915 align:middle line:84%
we can see much more precipitous
drops in the value of bonds

00:11:21.915 --> 00:11:24.584 align:middle line:90%
than even, you know, in the kind

00:11:24.584 --> 00:11:26.286 align:middle line:84%
of volatility we've
seen in equity.

00:11:26.286 --> 00:11:30.257 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly equities are looking
even less volatile than bonds,

00:11:30.257 --> 00:11:33.527 align:middle line:84%
and so if you're the managers
of the financial system,

00:11:33.527 --> 00:11:36.863 align:middle line:84%
that's a stampede
you want to prevent.

00:11:36.863 --> 00:11:39.900 align:middle line:84%
Now we've seen a series
of things we need to talk

00:11:39.900 --> 00:11:41.034 align:middle line:90%
about bank resolutions.

00:11:41.034 --> 00:11:42.636 align:middle line:90%
We've seen a series of things

00:11:42.636 --> 00:11:45.505 align:middle line:84%
that is making the retail
investor, the citizen,

00:11:45.505 --> 00:11:50.243 align:middle line:84%
nervous about the stability
of the financial system,

00:11:50.243 --> 00:11:51.878 align:middle line:84%
and one of the things
that happens

00:11:51.878 --> 00:11:54.347 align:middle line:84%
when that happens is they
start to buy precious metals.

00:11:54.347 --> 00:11:55.648 align:middle line:90%
Right. Right.

00:11:55.648 --> 00:11:59.119 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, and they
start to move their money

00:11:59.119 --> 00:12:01.188 align:middle line:90%
out of risk based investments.

00:12:01.188 --> 00:12:02.989 align:middle line:90%
They start to move out of bonds.

00:12:02.989 --> 00:12:06.159 align:middle line:84%
In February, I'll never
forget it, I went to one

00:12:06.159 --> 00:12:09.663 align:middle line:84%
of the services that
provides information

00:12:09.663 --> 00:12:13.300 align:middle line:84%
on different financial
products in February, and I...

00:12:13.300 --> 00:12:16.736 align:middle line:84%
because I never invest in the
